@page "/"
@using PureWave.Web.Data

<PageTitle>PureWave | Home Theatre Consultancy Durban</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Independent home theatre consultancy in Durban. PureWave helps you get better movies, better sound, and a room that feels worth every rand — without the guesswork." />
    <meta property="og:title" content="PureWave | Home Theatre Consultancy Durban" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Independent home theatre consultancy in Durban. Better movies, better sound, and a room that feels worth every rand." />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://www.purewaveacoustic.co.za/" />
</HeadContent>

<section class="hero-copy">
    <span class="section-tag">PureWave Consultancy</span>
    <h1>Better movie nights, better music, and a home theatre system that feels worth every rand.</h1>
    <p class="hero-lead">
        PureWave helps Durban homeowners build, upgrade, and fine-tune home theatre rooms that sound bigger, clearer, and more involving.
        Whether you want chesty bass for action films, clearer dialogue, or a system that finally does justice to your favourite music, the goal is simple:
        make the room more exciting to live with.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-tagline">Premium independent home theatre strategy, tuning, and integration.</p>
</section>

<section class="home-banner">
    <img src="/images/purewave-banner-medium.png" alt="PureWave Home Theatre Consultancy" />
</section>

<section class="hero-actions-strip">
    <a class="button-primary" href="/plans">Browse plans</a>
    <a class="button-secondary" href="/intake">Start the intake questionnaire</a>
</section>

<section class="stat-strip-section">
    <div class="stat-strip">
        <div>
            <strong>Independent</strong>
            <span>Advice based on what sounds right, not what a shop wants to move</span>
        </div>
        <div>
            <strong>Technical</strong>
            <span>Room planning, tuning, bass setup, projection, and smart control</span>
        </div>
        <div>
            <strong>Local</strong>
            <span>Durban, Umhlanga, Hillcrest, Westville and surrounds</span>
        </div>
        <div>
            <strong>Remote</strong>
            <span>Planning and procurement support for clients outside Durban</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="section-tag">Plans</span>
        <h2>Choose the kind of help that matches your room, your gear, and how seriously you take movie night.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="plan-preview-grid">
        @foreach (var plan in PureWavePlans.All)
        {
            <article class="plan-preview-card">
                <span class="section-tag">@plan.ServiceTrack</span>
                <span class="plan-accent">@plan.AccentLabel</span>
                <h3>@plan.Name</h3>
                <p>@plan.Tagline</p>
                <dl>
                    <div>
                        <dt>Best for</dt>
                        <dd>@plan.BestFor</dd>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <dt>Pricing</dt>
                        <dd>@plan.PricingModel</dd>
                    </div>
                </dl>
            </article>
        }
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-block section-band">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="section-tag">Remote Consultancy</span>
        <h2>Not in Durban? You can still get solid planning and buying advice remotely.</h2>
        <p>
            Remote support is an extra service track for clients who need help with layout planning, wiring priorities,
            and equipment choices before they start building or buying.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-band comparison-band-inline">
        <p>
            It starts with a WhatsApp conversation, then a remote slot is arranged at your convenience. You still come away with practical next steps
            for better movies, better sound, and a smarter upgrade path.
        </p>

        <a class="button-primary" href="/remote">Explore remote services</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href="/services">Smart home &amp; media</a>
        <a class="button-secondary"
           href="@SiteConfig.WhatsAppRemoteUrl"
           target="_blank"
           rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <WhatsAppIcon />
            Message on WhatsApp
        </a>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-block section-band">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="section-tag">Process</span>
        <h2>A simple process focused on getting you to a room that sounds and feels right.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="process-grid">
        <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Intake</h3>
            <p>You share the room, the gear, the problems, and what you want to enjoy more from movies and music.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Consult</h3>
            <p>PureWave helps make sense of the room and priorities, so the next decision is clearer and more confident.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Deliver</h3>
            <p>You get practical recommendations, tuning changes, or a full project roadmap depending on the plan you choose.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
    <div class="section-heading">
        <span class="section-tag">Sample Roadmap</span>
        <h2>See how a real system can grow from a solid start into a room that feels properly cinematic.</h2>
        <p>
            This example shows how PureWave thinks about upgrades: not as random product swaps, but as a step-by-step path toward bigger sound,
            deeper bass, and a more immersive room.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="comparison-band">
        <p>
            The roadmap starts with the front stage, then bass, then surrounds, then Atmos, so every upgrade actually makes the next one more worthwhile.
        </p>

        <a class="button-primary" href="/roadmap">View the upgrade roadmap</a>
    </div>
</section>
